                            <comment id="11893" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 29 Dec 2004 07:21:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added an analogous workaround to AbstractJasperReportsView: When writing to the OutputStream, it writes to a local ByteArrayOutputStream first to be able to set the content length header for IE.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please give a nightly 1.1.4-dev snapshot a try (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/downloads/nightly&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.springframework.org/downloads/nightly&lt;/a&gt;), if you have the chance to. As of tomorrow, the snapshot should contain this fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
